1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,366
hello everyone

2
00:00:01,366 --> 00:00:04,033
today we will do a quick GT:NH run

3
00:00:04,266 --> 00:00:09,766
to get started, we build a small shelter with the basic storage and survival stuff

4
00:00:09,900 --> 00:00:11,300
next we make a new room

5
00:00:11,300 --> 00:00:14,266
where we can place our first steam machines

6
00:00:14,266 --> 00:00:16,900
and once we get bigger steam machines

7
00:00:16,900 --> 00:00:19,766
we can also build a couple of blast furnaces

8
00:00:19,766 --> 00:00:24,366
this will allow us to produce the steel required for our low voltage workshop

9
00:00:24,366 --> 00:00:27,300
which can be used to craft an electric blast furnace

10
00:00:27,300 --> 00:00:30,500
to make the aluminium for the new MV machines

11
00:00:30,766 --> 00:00:33,833
all of that progression is taking a lot of resources

12
00:00:33,833 --> 00:00:35,866
which we are processing in the basement

13
00:00:35,866 --> 00:00:39,100
where we automated raw mineral sorting and processing

14
00:00:39,466 --> 00:00:40,966
to power all of that

15
00:00:40,966 --> 00:00:48,133
we are using four railcraft boilers fueled with charcoal blocks made from the wood produced by a spruce bonsai farm

16
00:00:48,133 --> 00:00:52,233
this setup will be enough for our additional blast furnaces

17
00:00:52,233 --> 00:00:57,466
and the new HV machines which can be used to assemble the parts for a rocket

18
00:00:57,833 --> 00:00:59,266
now that we have a rocket

19
00:00:59,266 --> 00:01:02,966
we can take off to new far places, such as the moon

20
00:01:03,266 --> 00:01:07,500
here we can find some rare materials that weren't abundant on earth

21
00:01:07,500 --> 00:01:09,766
like Bauxite and neodymium

22
00:01:09,900 --> 00:01:11,700
but most importantly

23
00:01:11,700 --> 00:01:15,033
we can now move to the garden dimension, a builder's heaven

24
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:18,600
where there are no hostile creatures, and it's always sunny

25
00:01:18,666 --> 00:01:22,100
the first thing we build here is a complete oil refinery

26
00:01:22,100 --> 00:01:24,866
which will yield all sorts of products

27
00:01:24,866 --> 00:01:27,566
after using those for our chemistry industry

28
00:01:27,566 --> 00:01:30,300
we use the leftover to fuel our new factory

29
00:01:30,633 --> 00:01:37,700
with that we can now power 16 blast furnaces and our new workshop equipped with all kinds of small machines

30
00:01:37,700 --> 00:01:41,200
that will allow us to craft anything we could possibly want

31
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:44,300
and to quickly process hundreds of items at once

32
00:01:44,300 --> 00:01:48,400
we also have a workshop section with some powerful multi blocks

33
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:52,433
the only issue left is to find a way of collecting enough raw materials

34
00:01:52,433 --> 00:01:55,466
to do so, we tried a different approach

35
00:01:55,466 --> 00:01:57,433
we did all sorts of weird rituals

36
00:01:57,433 --> 00:02:02,766
until we found a way of gathering materials that is easier than flying into space

37
00:02:02,833 --> 00:02:05,066
we make space rocks fly to us

38
00:02:05,066 --> 00:02:08,566
that way we can easily collect valuable materials

39
00:02:08,566 --> 00:02:10,600
without having to leave our base

40
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:13,466
to process all of those raw minerals

41
00:02:13,466 --> 00:02:17,966
we built an ore processing plant right next to the meteor crashing site

42
00:02:18,033 --> 00:02:22,100
next we do some further refinement in our chemical processing plant

43
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:26,500
and for those materials that still aren't ready for blast smelting

44
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:30,466
we have a place where can build longer refinement processing lines

45
00:02:30,466 --> 00:02:32,800
starting from the platinum line

46
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:36,000
however as you can see it's not working

47
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:39,000
and the issue seems to be a lack of hydrogen

48
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:41,700
since we need a planetary amount

49
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:44,700
the only solution is to go back to space again

50
00:02:45,033 --> 00:02:50,133
this time the target is the only place with enough hydrogen to satisfy our needs

51
00:02:50,133 --> 00:02:50,766
Jupiter

52
00:02:50,966 --> 00:02:55,700
to get the hydrogen, we build a space station equipped with a planetary gas siphon

53
00:02:55,700 --> 00:03:00,200
and start slowly pumping the whole gaseous planet towards our base

54
00:03:00,300 --> 00:03:03,966
with that, our platinum line is starting to work again

55
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:10,166
however platinum is not the only material that requires processing from a chain of machines

56
00:03:10,366 --> 00:03:13,800
we also had to set up a processing line for monazite

57
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:17,466
to obtain samarium cerium and other rare earth elements

58
00:03:17,466 --> 00:03:21,566
which we used to build a processing line for purifying naquadah

59
00:03:21,566 --> 00:03:25,766
finally, we also had to build a processing line for netherite

60
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:28,466
to power all of those new machines

61
00:03:28,466 --> 00:03:30,366
we are using only clean energy

62
00:03:30,366 --> 00:03:35,466
starting from a geothermal plant that produces steam from underground heat

63
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:37,700
next to our heat pumping station

64
00:03:37,700 --> 00:03:40,000
we also have a hydro electric plant

65
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:43,800
built on the slice of river that passes underneath our base

66
00:03:43,866 --> 00:03:47,566
but our main source of energy are eight wind turbines

67
00:03:47,633 --> 00:03:49,400
depending on wind strength

68
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:54,200

those can reach a power output peak of 560 kEU per tick


69
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:56,300
and if we fly higher

70
00:03:56,300 --> 00:03:59,500
we can see the start of our compressed solar panel array

71
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:01,866
which should outgrow our wind farm

72
00:04:02,100 --> 00:04:03,900
finally moving to the nether

73
00:04:03,900 --> 00:04:06,433
we are also using some nuclear reactors

74
00:04:06,433 --> 00:04:09,800
to power our ancient debris collection process

75
00:04:09,833 --> 00:04:15,400
those things are needed to build machines capable of withstanding temperatures higher than the sun

76
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:17,500
such as our new fusion reactor

77
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:19,000
but one was not enough

78
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:20,633
so we made another one

79
00:04:20,633 --> 00:04:21,800
and another one

80
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:22,966
and another one

81
00:04:22,966 --> 00:04:25,266
and then we scale those one tier up

82
00:04:25,266 --> 00:04:29,966
and we can use the old fusion reactors to boost our energy production

83
00:04:29,966 --> 00:04:34,866
but the real technological progress is that we can now get into quantum computing

84
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:39,433
after building our first small quantum computer and a research station

85
00:04:39,433 --> 00:04:42,066
we can start working on wetware circuits

86
00:04:42,066 --> 00:04:45,600
powerful enough to control UHV tier machines

87
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:49,633
but what we are actually going to want is a UV crops synthesizer

88
00:04:49,966 --> 00:04:54,133
which can be used to bait one of the best meteorites that can be achieved

89
00:04:54,133 --> 00:04:58,966
rich of all of the rarest minerals that normally don't even spawn in nature

90
00:04:59,066 --> 00:05:04,366
however while this is a great source of metals that we can't easily obtain by other means

91
00:05:04,366 --> 00:05:06,366
it has two huge downsides

92
00:05:06,366 --> 00:05:11,166
the first one is that summoning this meteor took the life of some sentient circuits

93
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:14,300
the second issue is that we have to physically dig it

94
00:05:14,466 --> 00:05:15,866
block by block

95
00:05:16,466 --> 00:05:18,033
to fix all those problems

96
00:05:18,033 --> 00:05:21,266
and also get a better selection of collected minerals

97
00:05:21,266 --> 00:05:23,400
we can move to our mega apiary

98
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:26,466
here we can beekeep some special breeds of bees

99
00:05:26,466 --> 00:05:28,966
that produce some high quality honeycombs

100
00:05:28,966 --> 00:05:32,033
from which we can extract all sorts of delicacies

101
00:05:32,033 --> 00:05:34,000
such as electric motors

102
00:05:34,633 --> 00:05:39,500
but there are still some materials we can't obtain easily from bees or meteors

103
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:44,466
like awakened draconium required for our next blast furnace upgrade

104
00:05:45,100 --> 00:05:48,366
we could obtain it by gambling on a new species of bee

105
00:05:48,366 --> 00:05:52,800
but since we aren't lobotomizing ourselves by grinding in a closed garden

106
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:56,633
we will simply catch the first vega B rocket passing by

107
00:05:56,966 --> 00:05:59,700
and once we get air dropped onto the new planet

108
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:02,833
we can quickly proceed into digging a hole to its core

109
00:06:02,833 --> 00:06:06,566
where we will be able to find small amounts of the needed material

110
00:06:06,900 --> 00:06:12,966
with that we can craft the royal bed required for the mutagen gene driven mating process of the Drake bee

111
00:06:13,233 --> 00:06:14,633
and as soon as it's ready

112
00:06:14,633 --> 00:06:16,666
we can move it to the mega apiary

113
00:06:16,766 --> 00:06:21,666
where it will quickly produce enough honeycombs to upgrade all of our volcanoes

114
00:06:22,166 --> 00:06:23,833
but even with that upgrade

115
00:06:23,833 --> 00:06:27,466
we still struggle keeping up with all of the blast smelting needed

116
00:06:27,466 --> 00:06:30,033
so we opted for a mega blast furnace

117
00:06:30,466 --> 00:06:34,900
the issue is that this giant machine will use a giant amount of energy

118
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:39,400
to keep up with that we built a couple of XL-plasma turbines

119
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:42,466
and while those managed to produce enough power

120
00:06:42,466 --> 00:06:45,200
the amount of fuel used became a new issue

121
00:06:45,466 --> 00:06:49,766
at first we tried to fix that by building more fusion reactors

122
00:06:49,766 --> 00:06:52,966
but this solution couldn't really match our consumption

123
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:55,666
so we designed a more compact solution

124
00:06:55,666 --> 00:06:59,966
a single giant reactor that can match hundreds of the smaller ones

125
00:06:59,966 --> 00:07:02,033
that solution worked really well

126
00:07:02,033 --> 00:07:08,200
until we realized that producing all of that plasma was using an amount of hydrogen bigger than Jupiter

127
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:11,566
and if the biggest planet of our solar system isn't enough

128
00:07:11,566 --> 00:07:15,766
the only thing left to do is pump fluids from all over the galaxy

129
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:20,266
but building space stations all over the galaxy is too much of a chore

130
00:07:20,266 --> 00:07:24,500
so we opted for a single giant space elevator in our base

131
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:29,866
equipped with a super powerful pump capable of suction in gases from the whole universe

132
00:07:29,866 --> 00:07:33,900
but building this pump requires some really strong materials

133
00:07:33,900 --> 00:07:37,000
leaving aside all of the neutronium and infinity

134
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:43,566
the real issue lies in the magnetic material required for the inner shaft of a motor powerful enough to spin such pump

135
00:07:43,566 --> 00:07:44,366
tengam

136
00:07:44,866 --> 00:07:47,400
just to catch a meteor with traces of it

137
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:49,433
we need an ion thruster jet

138
00:07:49,566 --> 00:07:52,100
but since this is quite expensive

139
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:55,466
instead of throwing it away for a dozen of tengam ores

140
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:58,000
we shall put it on our new improvised mother ship

141
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:01,866
to push it to a new galaxy where tengam spawns naturally

142
00:08:02,866 --> 00:08:04,633
and after a long voyage

143
00:08:04,633 --> 00:08:07,100
we got our mothership in the correct area

144
00:08:07,300 --> 00:08:09,633
now we can prepare a smaller shuttle

145
00:08:09,633 --> 00:08:12,600
which can be used to land on a tengam rich planet

146
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:15,200
where we quickly build a powerful void miner

147
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:17,800
with that we can conclude our space adventure

148
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:19,800
and relocate to our base

149
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:23,233
where we can start working on the powerful space pumps

150
00:08:23,266 --> 00:08:28,700
and it was then that we run for the first time into the infinit issue of not having enough infinity

151
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:30,900
to make one ingot of that material

152
00:08:30,900 --> 00:08:34,566
we currently need 11 stacks of Infinity catalyst dust

153
00:08:34,566 --> 00:08:37,633
which we are mainly collecting with space drones

154
00:08:37,766 --> 00:08:38,500
however

155
00:08:38,500 --> 00:08:43,800
not only the collection is still too slow even though we have multiple drones working on it

156
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:47,166
we are also low on diamonds and nether stars

157
00:08:47,233 --> 00:08:50,566
not to mention all of the cosmic neutronium required

158
00:08:50,566 --> 00:08:57,700
which will be a hard task even for our mega blast furnaces and freezers running at 100 million EU per tick each

159
00:08:57,700 --> 00:09:01,266
to fix all of those issues there is only one solution

160
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:04,433
a dimensionally transcendent Plasma Forge

161
00:09:04,433 --> 00:09:06,600
or dtpf for the homies

162
00:09:06,666 --> 00:09:11,033
this giant structure will melt pure infinity out of infinity catalyst

163
00:09:11,033 --> 00:09:14,833
completely removing the cost for neutronium and diamonds

164
00:09:14,833 --> 00:09:16,433
but don't be fooled

165
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:18,766
while the energy cost looks low

166
00:09:18,766 --> 00:09:22,500
it needs some excited dimensionally transcendent fuel

167
00:09:22,566 --> 00:09:30,900
and this innocent bucket of exotic material is a super high energy cost concentrate of a huge collection of nuclear fusion products

168
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:33,000
to produce enough of this fuel

169
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,866
we had to build a dedicated processing plant

170
00:09:35,866 --> 00:09:40,266
which of course was using more energy than we were producing

171
00:09:40,266 --> 00:09:42,633
so we upgraded our power plant

172
00:09:42,766 --> 00:09:48,866
but all of those things running on fusion products started to overwhelm our compact fusion reactors

173
00:09:48,866 --> 00:09:50,766
throttling our whole base

174
00:09:50,766 --> 00:09:53,866
it was clear that we were going to need more and more plasma

175
00:09:53,866 --> 00:09:57,900
and the Mark III reactor technology wasn't going to do it

176
00:09:57,900 --> 00:10:03,966
so we started working on a prototype of fusion reactor capable of achieving perfect overclock

177
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,433
with this structure

178
00:10:05,433 --> 00:10:08,966
we can now quickly craft millions of buckets of plasma

179
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,766
for all of our needs

180
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:14,766
which means that we have enough fuel to run a second dtpf

181
00:10:14,900 --> 00:10:17,466
this one will be equipped with Infinity Coils

182
00:10:17,466 --> 00:10:19,166
and run on higher power settings

183
00:10:19,166 --> 00:10:22,166
to quickly and cheaply craft all sort of things

184
00:10:22,166 --> 00:10:24,100
like neutronium from iron

185
00:10:24,233 --> 00:10:29,166
but the real game changer is that this machine will be able to craft tesseracts

186
00:10:29,300 --> 00:10:32,866
while the main usage for those is to produce transcendent metal

187
00:10:32,866 --> 00:10:36,500
what we are after is the energized tesseract technology

188
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:39,033
capable of wirelessly linking machines

189
00:10:39,033 --> 00:10:44,833
making it super easy for our matter manipulator to easily copy paste our production lines

190
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:47,966
building all of that was quite resource intensive

191
00:10:48,233 --> 00:10:54,600
so after building a water purification plant capable of producing subatomically perfected water

192
00:10:54,600 --> 00:11:00,400
we finally obtained the last ingredient required for the most energy intensive machine of the modpack

193
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:03,266
capable of making unlimited dtpf fuel

194
00:11:03,266 --> 00:11:06,000
the dimensionally transcendent plasma mixer

195
00:11:06,366 --> 00:11:09,000
this machine has unlimited mixing power

196
00:11:09,166 --> 00:11:11,300
or to better specify

197
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:13,600
the only limit is our power production

198
00:11:13,900 --> 00:11:16,700
indeed as soon as we turn it on 

199
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:20,366
in 5 seconds, it produced one day worth of dtpf fuel

200
00:11:20,366 --> 00:11:23,466
and also used two days worth of energy backup

201
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:28,366
and that made us realize that we might have some major energy production issue

202
00:11:28,666 --> 00:11:32,100
it was clear that we needed some better way of making energy

203
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:35,700
no matter how many more plasma turbines we will build

204
00:11:35,866 --> 00:11:40,666
no matter what kind of exotic metal we use for the blades of our turbines

205
00:11:40,766 --> 00:11:42,033
it won't be enough

206
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:50,233
and that's also because our Mark 4 fusion reactor barely keeps up with the plasma production with our current energy conversion rate

207
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:53,166
looking at the sky for a solution

208
00:11:53,166 --> 00:11:56,500
we peeked at a fusion reactor which might be big enough

209
00:11:56,700 --> 00:12:01,066
the only issue was figuring out a way of capturing all of that energy

210
00:12:01,233 --> 00:12:05,566
we figured out we could achieve that by enclosing the sun in a sphere of mirrors

211
00:12:05,566 --> 00:12:08,200
that will redirect all of its energy to our base

212
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:10,966
accomplishing such task was not easy

213
00:12:10,966 --> 00:12:17,300
especially because placing so many mirrors at that scale required a precision which no normal motor could achieve

214
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:20,100
luckily using some tessaracts

215
00:12:20,100 --> 00:12:24,866
we managed to create some four dimensional motors which were perfect for the task

216
00:12:25,366 --> 00:12:28,000
and once the Dyson sphere was completed

217
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:31,400
we managed to produce 1/3 of a trillion EU per tick

218
00:12:31,666 --> 00:12:35,033
since even superconductors couldn't move that much energy

219
00:12:35,033 --> 00:12:39,366
we had to use laser pipes to focus all of that energy in light form

220
00:12:39,466 --> 00:12:40,966
with that kind of power

221
00:12:40,966 --> 00:12:44,766
we managed to push our DTPFs at the limits of the universe

222
00:12:44,766 --> 00:12:47,300
synthesizing space time itself

223
00:12:47,433 --> 00:12:49,200
with this revolutionary material

224
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:54,566
we managed to build motors and pistons strong enough to compress things into a black hole

225
00:12:55,066 --> 00:12:58,000
and once we properly stabilized a black hole

226
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:02,000
we can use its gravitational field to compress whatever we want

227
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:05,700
thus we obtained unlimited amounts of super dense materials

228
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:07,866
such as eternal singularities

229
00:13:07,866 --> 00:13:10,400
which we can now use for mundane tasks

230
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:12,633
such as showering or storage

231
00:13:13,066 --> 00:13:20,100
one other usage for all of those singularities is the final tier of coils which will be with us for the rest of the game

232
00:13:20,100 --> 00:13:21,666
eternal coils

233
00:13:21,866 --> 00:13:25,700
with those we can unlock all of the dtpf recipes

234
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:31,666
and we shall start by making space time at 8 times the speed for 8 times less materials

235
00:13:31,866 --> 00:13:37,233
meanwhile we can use our old hypogen dtpfs to passively produce Infinity

236
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:40,100
at the moderate speed of 4 million liters per hour

237
00:13:40,100 --> 00:13:45,966
each with a recipe that uses only one Infinity catalyst for each stack of Infinity ingots

238
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:49,633
however that was also quickly draining all of our fuel

239
00:13:49,666 --> 00:13:54,933
and the issue was that our fusion reactors couldn't produce the ingredients fast enough

240
00:13:54,933 --> 00:13:59,800
it was obvious that we had to improve our fusion technology once again

241
00:13:59,866 --> 00:14:03,633
so we started working on the final type of fusion coils

242
00:14:03,633 --> 00:14:07,233
and after the initial examination of the crafting plan

243
00:14:07,233 --> 00:14:09,233
between all of the missing ingredients

244
00:14:09,233 --> 00:14:11,300
we noticed that once again

245
00:14:11,300 --> 00:14:14,233
our platinum line is having trouble keeping up

246
00:14:14,366 --> 00:14:17,700
this time we couldn't pinpoint a specific issue

247
00:14:17,866 --> 00:14:23,500
this gigantic cluster of machines is just too convoluted and slow for our needs

248
00:14:23,533 --> 00:14:28,766
so after quickly reanalyzing the design of our platline, looking for improvements

249
00:14:28,766 --> 00:14:31,200
we realized we can just scratch all of that

250
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:35,766
and use force to quantum the platinum out of unrefined metal dusts

251
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:37,833
and there is our new platline

252
00:14:38,033 --> 00:14:42,233
a single machine that can be speed up by simply tweaking the input power

253
00:14:42,433 --> 00:14:46,833
and now that we are refining platinum at 100 times the speed

254
00:14:46,833 --> 00:14:50,900
we can't help but want to improve our other processing lines

255
00:14:51,166 --> 00:14:52,666
after quickly doing so

256
00:14:52,666 --> 00:14:58,100
we realized that this incredible machine can also replace all of our bacterial vats

257
00:14:58,433 --> 00:15:01,466
after reimagining all of our processing lines

258
00:15:01,466 --> 00:15:05,600
the only thing missing for our new fusion reactor was dragon blood

259
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:10,500
now while hunting dragons is a nice activity to keep your body engaged

260
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:13,233
it's not a reliable source of dragon blood

261
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:14,966
considering our needs

262
00:15:14,966 --> 00:15:17,433
even with the infinite world generation

263
00:15:17,433 --> 00:15:20,966
we would still put this species at risk of extinction

264
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:25,033
looking for a solution we invited some friends over

265
00:15:25,233 --> 00:15:27,433
they then proceeded into summoning a demon

266
00:15:27,433 --> 00:15:30,033
who traded its heart for some emeralds

267
00:15:30,233 --> 00:15:32,766
we used that to craft an infinity egg

268
00:15:32,766 --> 00:15:36,266
capable of producing an infinite amount of dragon blood

269
00:15:36,966 --> 00:15:42,833
with that, we finally managed to build our compact fusion reactor Mark 5 final type

270
00:15:43,366 --> 00:15:45,633
and with all of that fusing power

271
00:15:45,633 --> 00:15:48,500
our plasma fuel production skyrocketed

272
00:15:48,500 --> 00:15:52,100
allowing for a huge expansion of our dtpf cluster

273
00:15:52,366 --> 00:15:54,400
with so many plasma forges

274
00:15:54,400 --> 00:16:00,400
we can now produce enough infinity, space time and shirabon to mass produce quantum circuits

275
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:04,966
the highest tier of circuit capable of controlling UXV machinery

276
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:09,266
and that means that we can now spam wireless energy hatches

277
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:14,766
now we can just press Ctrl C, Ctrl V and make our base grow exponentially

278
00:16:14,766 --> 00:16:17,000
without having to connect any cable

279
00:16:17,266 --> 00:16:23,500
however an exponential amount of new machines requires an exponential amount of extra energy production

280
00:16:23,866 --> 00:16:28,033
and while building more Dyson Spheres doesn't require much effort

281
00:16:28,033 --> 00:16:32,066
crafting all of the parts requires a lot of transcendent metal

282
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:37,800
currently we are blasting that material with the power of three Dyson spheres

283
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:40,366
but it seems to still be far from enough

284
00:16:40,900 --> 00:16:44,400
and it was exactly when every hope was lost to darkness

285
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:47,466
that a new light brightened our blast's melting area

286
00:16:47,966 --> 00:16:50,600
it was not our fusion reactor blowing up

287
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:53,566
but a forge sent directly from the gods

288
00:16:53,900 --> 00:16:55,766
and in this gigantic machine

289
00:16:55,766 --> 00:17:01,166
we found a module capable of quickly processing all of our transcendental materials

290
00:17:01,366 --> 00:17:03,433
and to show the gods our gratitude

291
00:17:03,433 --> 00:17:06,766
we decided to build the biggest pyramid ever in their honor

292
00:17:07,033 --> 00:17:10,366
to do so we needed huge amounts of stone

293
00:17:10,366 --> 00:17:16,300
and the best way of gathering it seems to be placing a whole planet inside something called eye of harmony

294
00:17:16,900 --> 00:17:21,400
while crafting all of the parts for such a marvelous machine isn't too easy

295
00:17:21,466 --> 00:17:24,033
putting everything together is the main issue

296
00:17:24,566 --> 00:17:26,666
since we have no time to waste

297
00:17:26,666 --> 00:17:34,366
we are going to shove the energy produced by six Dyson Spheres into our assembly lines to speed up the crafting process

298
00:17:34,733 --> 00:17:37,066
and after not too much time

299
00:17:37,066 --> 00:17:39,866
we managed to complete our first eye of harmony

300
00:17:40,166 --> 00:17:46,300
that machine will take two hours to produce 240 millions units of stone dust

301
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:48,233
that sounds like a lot

302
00:17:48,233 --> 00:17:52,500
but considering we already had 9 billions it's not

303
00:17:52,700 --> 00:17:54,900
if we truly want to impress the gods

304
00:17:54,900 --> 00:17:57,866
we have to improve our space time compression technology

305
00:17:57,866 --> 00:18:02,033
to the point where our eye of harmony is capable of containing the deep♂dark

306
00:18:02,033 --> 00:18:05,900
thus harnessing more than 1 billion stone dusts at once

307
00:18:06,033 --> 00:18:08,766
however that won't fix the speed issue

308
00:18:08,766 --> 00:18:10,833
if anything it will make it worse

309
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:15,266
so if we want the process to be done in a tolerable amount of time

310
00:18:15,266 --> 00:18:18,966
we also have to improve our time dilation technology

311
00:18:19,300 --> 00:18:21,466
doing so is no easy task

312
00:18:21,833 --> 00:18:25,700
the first issue we noticed is the amount of infinity required

313
00:18:25,700 --> 00:18:34,433
luckily, after 8 hours of working towards fully breaching dimensional boundaries, and with the help of a transdimensional alignment matrix

314
00:18:34,433 --> 00:18:36,766
our dtpfs achieved full convergence

315
00:18:36,766 --> 00:18:39,166
thus acquiring perfect overclock

316
00:18:39,166 --> 00:18:44,100
that made our Infinity production skyrocket to 5 billions liters per hour

317
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:47,900
but this comes with a huge cost a lot of plasma fuel

318
00:18:47,966 --> 00:18:53,166
so much that even a full tower of final type fusion reactors couldn't keep up with that

319
00:18:53,266 --> 00:18:54,366
thanks god

320
00:18:54,366 --> 00:19:00,433
his forge can be equipped with a plasma fabricator module which was just enough for our needs

321
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:04,600
with that, we finally managed to build our first eye of harmony

322
00:19:04,600 --> 00:19:07,633
which however, was still too slow

323
00:19:07,833 --> 00:19:11,800
we could speed it up with better time dilation field generators

324
00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:13,800
but those cost dwarf matter

325
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:16,766
only produced by the eye of harmony itself

326
00:19:16,833 --> 00:19:19,900
the only solution left was to overclock the machine

327
00:19:19,900 --> 00:19:23,566
which means 4 times the energy for twice the speed

328
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:27,233
and that caused once again energy issues

329
00:19:27,233 --> 00:19:30,366
this time the scale of the problem is huge

330
00:19:30,466 --> 00:19:33,300
as large as the number of stars in the sky

331
00:19:33,300 --> 00:19:35,666
since we built so many Dyson spheres

332
00:19:35,666 --> 00:19:38,100
that there are no more stars to use

333
00:19:38,100 --> 00:19:41,466
there was only one thing left to try, antimatter

334
00:19:42,033 --> 00:19:44,666
after producing a decent amount of that stuff

335
00:19:44,666 --> 00:19:48,266
we can slam it in the Slam to quickly charge up our batteries

336
00:19:48,266 --> 00:19:55,666
all was left to do was to figure out the correct balance between antimatter production and eye of harmony overclocking

337
00:19:56,066 --> 00:20:01,500
the correct solution turned out to be that we should just keep building more antimatter sequences

338
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:05,266
until our eye of harmony finally reached the gallifreyan tier

339
00:20:05,633 --> 00:20:08,500
and of course, one was not enough

340
00:20:08,900 --> 00:20:14,233
actually not even 20 eye of harmony were enough for our future projects

341
00:20:14,266 --> 00:20:16,100
we needed more stone dust

342
00:20:16,100 --> 00:20:18,166
and this approach was too slow

343
00:20:18,466 --> 00:20:23,866
the solution we figured out was to compress an eye of harmony into an astral array fabricator

344
00:20:23,866 --> 00:20:26,666
thus exponentially increasing production

345
00:20:26,900 --> 00:20:32,433
and that reminded us that stone dust is not the only thing we are getting from this microverse

346
00:20:32,566 --> 00:20:35,833
we are indeed getting a lot of raw stellar plasma mixture

347
00:20:35,833 --> 00:20:40,100
which we can use to fuel and empower the gorgeous forge of the gods

348
00:20:40,566 --> 00:20:42,433
by increasing the fuel we burn

349
00:20:42,433 --> 00:20:45,400
we can indeed boost the power of its furnaces

350
00:20:45,433 --> 00:20:49,400
but what really matters is that we are showing our devotion to the deities

351
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:52,700
helping us progress in our path of transcendence

352
00:20:52,966 --> 00:20:57,100
and that reminded us that we should prepare our gift in a proper package

353
00:20:57,333 --> 00:21:00,000
so after charging up an Error-tier battery

354
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:04,800
we started packaging our stone into an artificial universe storage cell

355
00:21:05,466 --> 00:21:08,833
and only then we realized a fatal misunderstanding

356
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:14,200
we can't gift the greatest pyramid ever because we are constantly producing more of it

357
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:17,666
and since our production keeps growing exponentially

358
00:21:17,666 --> 00:21:21,700
any gift would look like a joke compared to what we could do the day after

359
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:26,433
but after being lost in the labyrinth of our thoughts for a scary amount of time

360
00:21:26,433 --> 00:21:29,166
we finally saw a light at the end of the tunnel

361
00:21:29,666 --> 00:21:32,066
we don't have to make a single package

362
00:21:32,066 --> 00:21:34,200
we can do a constant delivery

363
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:35,500
but of course

364
00:21:35,500 --> 00:21:40,200
reaching the dimension beyond the stars will require a really strong portal

365
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:41,233
a star gate

366
00:21:41,233 --> 00:21:46,500
the issue is that transcendent motors don't have the strength required to carry our gift

367
00:21:46,500 --> 00:21:53,600
while space time motors don't have the extra dimensional capability to reach dimensions beyond our comprehension

368
00:21:53,833 --> 00:21:56,433
we needed to design a new kind of motor

369
00:21:56,600 --> 00:22:03,600
this time we started by mixing together the four basic substances of reality, obtaining primordial matter

370
00:22:03,866 --> 00:22:07,100
with that and some other rather complicated materials

371
00:22:07,100 --> 00:22:09,800
we create some universium nanites

372
00:22:10,066 --> 00:22:13,700
then we move from the nanite forge to the implosion compressor

373
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:21,666
where we blow those nanites inside some condensed stelar plasma mixture magneto hydrodynamically constraining it

374
00:22:21,800 --> 00:22:24,900
that material will be the foundation of our new motors

375
00:22:24,900 --> 00:22:28,433
but we need something to properly mold such impossible fluid

376
00:22:28,433 --> 00:22:34,000
and quantum forcing some eternity out of primordial matter seems to do the trick

377
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:36,100
but to properly meld everything together

378
00:22:36,100 --> 00:22:38,266
we had to use an implosion compressor

379
00:22:38,266 --> 00:22:42,000
and add some advanced technology to contain the new material

380
00:22:42,100 --> 00:22:44,166
and after putting everything together

381
00:22:44,166 --> 00:22:49,366
we finally obtained a motor strong enough for the delivery of the biggest ever growing pyramid

382
00:22:49,866 --> 00:22:53,066
all was left to do was to produce enough of those motors

383
00:22:53,066 --> 00:22:56,433
so we had to do several upgrades to our factory

384
00:22:56,566 --> 00:23:00,200
we started by checking if our fusion tower was good enough

385
00:23:00,233 --> 00:23:03,833
then we added more astral arrays to our eyes of harmony

386
00:23:04,100 --> 00:23:06,766
next we built more assembly lines

387
00:23:06,933 --> 00:23:09,900
then we added more astral arrays to our eyes of harmony

388
00:23:09,900 --> 00:23:10,966
more assembly lines

389
00:23:30,500 --> 00:23:34,033
and after going through every single side quest we were given

390
00:23:34,033 --> 00:23:37,000
we are finally ready to defeat the final boss

391
00:23:37,166 --> 00:23:43,766
to do so we first merge all of our eyes of harmony into a single one with 1000 Astral arrays

392
00:23:43,966 --> 00:23:49,600
then we use a draconic reactor configuration that should not be seen by naked mortal eyes

393
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:54,633
to produce enough chaos shards to get a couple of singularity crafting storages

394
00:23:54,633 --> 00:23:57,466
so that we can one step craft the Stargate

395
00:23:57,600 --> 00:24:03,500
finally, we use the secret technique of the double matter manipulator to complete the final challenge

396
00:24:03,900 --> 00:24:06,300
and exactly when we thought we were done

397
00:24:06,300 --> 00:24:11,066
we realized that the real value here is not in the giant pile of stone dust

398
00:24:11,066 --> 00:24:13,500
but in the machines we built along the way

399
00:24:13,833 --> 00:24:18,633
so following the random comments coming from whatever place this gate leads to

400
00:24:18,633 --> 00:24:22,433
we decided to take one extra step and make 10 more star gates

401
00:24:22,433 --> 00:24:30,566
and after one week of pushing our factory at the limits of the computation capacity of the simulation we call reality

402
00:24:30,566 --> 00:24:33,300
we finally managed to complete the task

403
00:24:33,833 --> 00:24:38,200
and with that, I think our factory is now good enough to keep growing on its own

404
00:24:38,200 --> 00:24:41,466
so we can fly away to the next adventure

405
00:24:41,666 --> 00:24:42,600
bye bye

406
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:01,366
大家好

407
00:00:01,366 --> 00:00:04,033
今天我们要速通GTNH

408
00:00:04,266 --> 00:00:09,766
首先，我们建一个有基本的储物和生存用品的小庇护所

409
00:00:09,900 --> 00:00:11,300
接下来我们做一个新房间

410
00:00:11,300 --> 00:00:14,266
在那里我们可以放置第一台蒸汽机器

411
00:00:14,266 --> 00:00:16,900
一旦我们有了更大的蒸汽机器

412
00:00:16,900 --> 00:00:19,766
我们还可以建几个砖高炉

413
00:00:19,766 --> 00:00:24,366
这将使我们能够生产 LV 车间所需的钢材

414
00:00:24,366 --> 00:00:27,300
这些钢材可以用来制造一个电高炉

415
00:00:27,300 --> 00:00:30,500
用来给新的 MV 机器制造铝

416
00:00:30,766 --> 00:00:33,833
所有这些进展需要大量的资源

417
00:00:33,833 --> 00:00:35,866
而我们正在地下室处理它们

418
00:00:35,866 --> 00:00:39,100
我们在这自动化原矿分拣和加工

419
00:00:39,466 --> 00:00:40,966
为了给这一切供能

420
00:00:40,966 --> 00:00:48,133
我们使用四个RC锅炉，用云杉木农场
生产的木材制成的木炭块作为燃料

421
00:00:48,133 --> 00:00:57,466
这个装置对我们额外的高炉
和能够用于组装火箭零件的新HV机器来说足够了

422
00:00:57,833 --> 00:00:59,266
既然我们有了火箭

423
00:00:59,266 --> 00:01:02,966
我们可以飞到新的地方，比如月球

424
00:01:03,266 --> 00:01:07,500

我们可以在这里找到一些地球上比较稀少的矿物


425
00:01:07,500 --> 00:01:09,766
像铝土矿和钕

426
00:01:09,900 --> 00:01:11,700
但最重要的是

427
00:01:11,700 --> 00:01:15,033
我们现在可以搬进"花园维度"，一个建筑师的天堂

428
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:18,600
那里没有敌对的生物，总是阳光明媚

429
00:01:18,666 --> 00:01:22,100
我们首先要建的是一个完整的炼油厂

430
00:01:22,100 --> 00:01:24,866

用于产出各类化工产品


431
00:01:24,866 --> 00:01:27,566

在把这些产品投入化工生产后


432
00:01:27,566 --> 00:01:30,300
我们把剩余的产物用来给新工厂供能

433
00:01:30,633 --> 00:01:37,700
有了这些，我们现在可以驱动 16 座高炉
还有一整间装满各种小型机器的新车间

434
00:01:37,700 --> 00:01:41,200
这样我们几乎想做什么都能做出来了

435
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:44,300
为了一次性高速处理上百个物品

436
00:01:44,300 --> 00:01:48,400
车间里还有一块摆满了各种强力多方块机器的区域

437
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:52,433
唯一剩下的问题是收集到足够的原材料

438
00:01:52,433 --> 00:01:55,466
为此，我们尝试了不同的方法

439
00:01:55,466 --> 00:01:57,433
我们做了各种稀奇古怪的"仪式"

440
00:01:57,433 --> 00:02:02,766
直到我们找到了一种比亲自飞到太空还要轻松的收集方式

441
00:02:02,833 --> 00:02:05,066
我们让太空里的石头自己飞过来

442
00:02:05,066 --> 00:02:08,566
这样我们可以很容易地收集到有价值的材料

443
00:02:08,566 --> 00:02:10,600
而且完全不用离开基地

444
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:13,466
为了处理这些粗矿

445
00:02:13,466 --> 00:02:17,966
我们就在陨石坠落点旁边建了一座矿石处理工厂

446
00:02:18,033 --> 00:02:22,100
接着再送到化工厂里做进一步的精炼

447
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:26,500
而对于那些还不适合丢进高炉冶炼的材料

448
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:30,466
我们还有一片地方可以搭建更长的精炼产线

449
00:02:30,466 --> 00:02:32,800
从铂产线开始

450
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:36,000
不过如你所见，它现在并不在工作

451
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:39,000
看起来问题是氢气不够

452
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:41,700
毕竟我们需要的是行星级的用量

453
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:44,700
唯一的办法就是再上一次太空

454
00:02:45,033 --> 00:02:50,133
这次的目标，是唯一能提供足够氢气来满足我们需求的地方

455
00:02:50,133 --> 00:02:50,766
木星

456
00:02:50,966 --> 00:02:55,700
为了得到氢气，我们建了一座装有行星气体钻机的空间站

457
00:02:55,700 --> 00:03:00,200
慢慢把整颗气态行星抽到我们的基地

458
00:03:00,300 --> 00:03:03,966
这样一来，我们的铂产线又开始运转起来了

459
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:10,166
不过，需要整条生产线来处理的可不止铂这一种材料

460
00:03:10,366 --> 00:03:13,800
我们还得搭一条独居石处理线

461
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:17,466
用它来提炼钐、铈以及其他稀土元素

462
00:03:17,466 --> 00:03:21,566

这些稀土元素又用于建造硅岩净化处理线


463
00:03:21,566 --> 00:03:25,766

最后，我们还必须为下界合金建造一条处理线


464
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:28,466
为了给这一大堆新机器供电

465
00:03:28,466 --> 00:03:30,366
我们只使用清洁能源

466
00:03:30,366 --> 00:03:35,466
先是靠深地热泵，用地下热量来产蒸汽

467
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:37,700
在热泵旁边

468
00:03:37,700 --> 00:03:40,000
我们还有一个水力发电厂

469
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:43,800
就修在穿过基地下方的那条河上

470
00:03:43,866 --> 00:03:47,566
不过，我们的主力电源是八台风力涡轮机

471
00:03:47,633 --> 00:03:49,400
输出则要看风力强弱

472
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:54,200
这些最多能做到 560 kEU/t 的峰值输出

473
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:56,300
如果我们飞得更高

474
00:03:56,300 --> 00:03:59,500

就能看到我们压缩太阳能板阵列中建好的第一台设备


475
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:01,866
它以后的规模应该会超过风电场

476
00:04:02,100 --> 00:04:03,900
最后我们来到下界

477
00:04:03,900 --> 00:04:06,433
在那儿我们也用上了几座核反应堆

478
00:04:06,433 --> 00:04:09,800

给远古残骸的采集供能


479
00:04:09,833 --> 00:04:15,400
远古残骸是用来造"能承受比太阳
还高温度的机器"的关键材料

480
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:17,500
比如我们新的聚变反应堆

481
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:19,000
但只造一台根本不够

482
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:20,633
所以我们又做了一台

483
00:04:20,633 --> 00:04:21,800
双来一台

484
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:22,966
叒来一台

485
00:04:22,966 --> 00:04:25,266
然后再把它们都提升一个等级

486
00:04:25,266 --> 00:04:29,966
旧的聚变堆还能拿来增加发电量

487
00:04:29,966 --> 00:04:34,866
不过真正的技术飞跃是我们终于可以踏入量子计算领域了

488
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:39,433
在造出第一台小型量子计算机和研究站之后

489
00:04:39,433 --> 00:04:42,066
我们就可以着手研究湿件电路了

490
00:04:42,066 --> 00:04:45,600

强到足以控制 UHV 电压的机器


491
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:49,633
但我们真正想要的是一台UV 作物合成机

492
00:04:49,966 --> 00:04:54,133
它可以"钓"出游戏里能弄到的顶级陨石之一

493
00:04:54,133 --> 00:04:58,966
里面有很多极其稀有、不会自然生成的矿石

494
00:04:59,066 --> 00:05:04,366
尽管这是获得其他方式难以取得的金属的好方法

495
00:05:04,366 --> 00:05:06,366
但它也有两个非常致命的缺点

496
00:05:06,366 --> 00:05:11,166

第一，召唤这块陨石的时候，会牺牲几块有知觉的电路


497
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:14,300
第二，这玩意儿得我们自己上手挖

498
00:05:14,466 --> 00:05:15,866
一格一格地挖

499
00:05:16,466 --> 00:05:18,033
想把这些问题一起解决

500
00:05:18,033 --> 00:05:21,266
顺便把产出的矿物搭配也优化一下

501
00:05:21,266 --> 00:05:23,400
该巨型工业蜂箱出场了

502
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:26,466
在这里我们可以养一些特殊品种的蜜蜂

503
00:05:26,466 --> 00:05:28,966
它们会产出各种高品质蜂巢

504
00:05:28,966 --> 00:05:32,033
我们可以从中提取各种美味佳肴

505
00:05:32,033 --> 00:05:34,000
比如电动马达

506
00:05:34,633 --> 00:05:39,500
不过有些材料，靠蜜蜂和陨石依然不太好搞到

507
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:44,466
比如下一次高炉升级要用的觉醒龙锭

508
00:05:45,100 --> 00:05:48,366

理论上我们可以搏一搏杂交出新蜜蜂品种


509
00:05:48,366 --> 00:05:52,800
但我们又不打算在封闭花园里把自己无脑肝成植物人

510
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:56,633

我们赶一班路过的前往织女一的火箭就行


511
00:05:56,966 --> 00:05:59,700
被空投到那颗新星球上之后

512
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:02,833
我们快速下挖，直至星核

513
00:06:02,833 --> 00:06:06,566
在那附近就能找到少量我们需要的材料

514
00:06:06,900 --> 00:06:12,966
拿这些材料就能做出皇家蜂床
用来完成恶龙蜂那套靠诱变基因驱动的繁殖流程

515
00:06:13,233 --> 00:06:14,633
东西一旦做好

516
00:06:14,633 --> 00:06:16,666
我们立刻把它放入巨型工业蜂箱

517
00:06:16,766 --> 00:06:21,666
很快就能产出一大批蜂巢，把我们所有的炽焱高炉统统升级

518
00:06:22,166 --> 00:06:23,833
可就算有了这些升级

519
00:06:23,833 --> 00:06:27,466
想跟上高炉冶炼的需求还是有点吃力

520
00:06:27,466 --> 00:06:30,033
所以我们干脆上一个巨型高炉

521
00:06:30,466 --> 00:06:34,900
问题是，这玩意儿吃电也巨离谱

522
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:39,400
为了喂饱它，我们造了几台特大等离子涡轮

523
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:42,466
这些机器的发电量倒是堪堪够用

524
00:06:42,466 --> 00:06:45,200
但消耗的燃料量又变成新的大坑

525
00:06:45,466 --> 00:06:49,766
一开始我们想多造点聚变堆把问题糊过去

526
00:06:49,766 --> 00:06:52,966
但这套方案还是跟不上我们恐怖的用电量

527
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:55,666

于是我们又设计了一版紧凑的方案


528
00:06:55,666 --> 00:06:59,966
一台顶得上几百台小号反应堆的巨型反应堆

529
00:06:59,966 --> 00:07:02,033
一开始效果确实相当不错

530
00:07:02,033 --> 00:07:08,200
直到我们发现，为了产出这么多等离子
消耗的氢气量已经比一整颗木星还多

531
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:11,566
要是连太阳系里最大的行星都不够榨

532
00:07:11,566 --> 00:07:15,766
那就只能去其他星系抽流体了

533
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:20,266
可在其他星系建空间站，这工作量也太离谱了

534
00:07:20,266 --> 00:07:24,500
于是我们选择在基地里竖一根巨型太空电梯

535
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:29,866

加一台超级抽气泵，能把整个宇宙的气体都往这边吸


536
00:07:29,866 --> 00:07:33,900
不过要造这玩意儿，需要的材料强度离谱

537
00:07:33,900 --> 00:07:37,000
先不提那些中子、无尽之类的材料

538
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:43,566
真正卡人的，是能让这台泵转起来的马达内轴用的磁性材料

539
00:07:43,566 --> 00:07:44,366
——纯镃

540
00:07:44,866 --> 00:07:47,400
光是要抓一块带点纯镃的陨石

541
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:49,433
我们就得先造一台离子推进喷口

542
00:07:49,566 --> 00:07:52,100
但因为那东西真的很贵

543
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:55,466

与其为了一些纯镃矿就扔掉这个喷口


544
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:58,000
那不如直接把它装到一艘我们临时凑出来的母舰上

545
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:01,866
把整艘母舰推进到一个能自然生成纯镃的新星系去

546
00:08:02,866 --> 00:08:04,633
在太空里漂泊了好一阵之后

547
00:08:04,633 --> 00:08:07,100
我们总算把母舰开到了目标星域

548
00:08:07,300 --> 00:08:09,633
接下来就可以准备一艘小型穿梭机

549
00:08:09,633 --> 00:08:12,600
坐它降落到一颗纯镃储量丰富的行星上

550
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:15,200
在那里快速架一台高配虚空采矿厂

551
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:17,800
搞定这些之后，这一趟太空冒险就可以收尾了

552
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:19,800
然后我们打道回府

553
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:23,233
回到基地，就能正式开工造那台真正的宇宙级气泵

554
00:08:23,266 --> 00:08:28,700
就在此时，我们第一次遇到无尽的"无尽锭不够用"的问题

555
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:30,900
现在要做出一块无尽锭

556
00:08:30,900 --> 00:08:34,566
光是无尽催化剂粉就要用掉 11 组

557
00:08:34,566 --> 00:08:37,633
这些主要是靠各种太空无人机一点点搬回来的

558
00:08:37,766 --> 00:08:38,500
然而

559
00:08:38,500 --> 00:08:43,800
就算已经派了好几架无人机在干，收集速度还是太慢

560
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:47,166
我们手上的钻石和下界之星也库存见底

561
00:08:47,233 --> 00:08:50,566
更别提还要准备一大堆宇宙中子态素

562
00:08:50,566 --> 00:08:57,700
就算我们那几座巨高炉和冷冻机吃一亿 EU/t
这任务还是难到爆炸

563
00:08:57,700 --> 00:09:01,266
要把这些问题一网打尽，其实只有一个解法

564
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:04,433
那就是——超维度等离子锻炉

565
00:09:04,433 --> 00:09:06,600
或者简称 DTPF

566
00:09:06,666 --> 00:09:11,033
这座庞然大物可以把无尽催化剂直接熔成无尽

567
00:09:11,033 --> 00:09:14,833
这样做就完全不用消耗中子和钻石了

568
00:09:14,833 --> 00:09:16,433
不过别被表面数据骗了

569
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:18,766
从配方上看，它本身吃电其实不算多

570
00:09:18,766 --> 00:09:22,500
关键是它需要激发的超维度燃料

571
00:09:22,566 --> 00:09:30,900
这一小桶看起来人畜无害的异星催化剂
是把一大堆能量密度高得离谱的核聚变产物经浓缩得到的

572
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:33,000
为了生产出足够多这种燃料

573
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,866
我们不得不专门给它建一整座加工厂

574
00:09:35,866 --> 00:09:40,266
而这工厂自己吃的电，当然是比整个基地发的电还多

575
00:09:40,266 --> 00:09:42,633
于是我们只好再把整个发电系统升级一轮

576
00:09:42,766 --> 00:09:48,866
不过所有这些靠聚变产物运转的玩意儿
已经快把那几台紧凑型聚变堆压垮了

577
00:09:48,866 --> 00:09:50,766
限制了我们整个基地的产能

578
00:09:50,766 --> 00:09:53,866
很明显，接下来我们只会需要越来越多的等离子体

579
00:09:53,866 --> 00:09:57,900
而三阶反应堆已经完全撑不住了

580
00:09:57,900 --> 00:10:03,966
所以我们开始研究一台可以实现完美超频的聚变原型机

581
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,433
有了这台机器后

582
00:10:05,433 --> 00:10:08,966
我们现在可以非常快地造出几百万桶等离子体

583
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,766
基本能满足我们的需求了

584
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:14,766
这也意味着，燃料多到可以再养活第二台 DTPF 了

585
00:10:14,900 --> 00:10:17,466
这一台会装上无尽线圈

586
00:10:17,466 --> 00:10:19,166
并以更高功率运行

587
00:10:19,166 --> 00:10:22,166
用来又快又省地合成各种材料

588
00:10:22,166 --> 00:10:24,100
比如直接把普通铁炼成中子

589
00:10:24,233 --> 00:10:29,166
但真正让游戏质变的是，这机器能直接做超立方体

590
00:10:29,300 --> 00:10:32,866
尽管超立方体的主要用途是做超时空金属

591
00:10:32,866 --> 00:10:36,500
不过我们真正看上的是充能超立方体解锁的科技

592
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:39,033
它可以在机器之间建立无线链接

593
00:10:39,033 --> 00:10:44,833
让物质操纵者复制粘贴整条产线
变得跟按 Ctrl+C／Ctrl+V 一样简单

594
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:47,966
把这一整套系统堆出来，资源消耗自然是夸张到不行

595
00:10:48,233 --> 00:10:54,600
所以我们又建了一座净水厂，能生产出亚原子级纯净水

596
00:10:54,600 --> 00:11:00,400
这才终于凑齐了整合包里那台
最吃电力的机器所需要的最后一种材料

597
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:03,266
那台机器可以源源不断地制造 DTPF 用的燃料

598
00:11:03,266 --> 00:11:06,000
它名叫超维度等离子搅拌机

599
00:11:06,366 --> 00:11:09,000
理论上这玩意儿的混合能力是没有上限的

600
00:11:09,166 --> 00:11:11,300
更确切地说

601
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:13,600
唯一的上限是我们能发多少电

602
00:11:13,900 --> 00:11:16,700
实际上，这东西一旦开机

603
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:20,366
不到 5 秒就搅出了够 DTPF 用一整天的燃料

604
00:11:20,366 --> 00:11:23,466
顺手把我们两天份的电力储备一口气榨干

605
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:28,366
于是我们不得不承认：
在发电这一块，大抵是有严重问题的

606
00:11:28,666 --> 00:11:32,100
很明显，我们必须找一套更靠谱的发电方案

607
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:35,700
无论再多造多少台等离子涡轮

608
00:11:35,866 --> 00:11:40,666
更别提给涡轮叶片换上多离谱的稀有金属

609
00:11:40,766 --> 00:11:42,033
最终都还是完全不够看

610
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:50,233
再加上以现在这点能量转换效率，
就连四阶聚变堆都几乎跟不上等离子体的产量

611
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:53,166
于是我们只好抬头寻找答案

612
00:11:53,166 --> 00:11:56,500

我们一眼瞟见一个可能够大的聚变反应堆


613
00:11:56,700 --> 00:12:01,066
唯一的问题是想办法把那些能量全收集下来

614
00:12:01,233 --> 00:12:05,566

我们想到可以通过用球状排列的镜子包住太阳来实现这一点


615
00:12:05,566 --> 00:12:08,200
把太阳辐射出的能量全部反射到我们的基地

616
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:10,966
要做到这件事当然一点也不轻松

617
00:12:10,966 --> 00:12:17,300
尤其是在那种尺度下摆这么多镜子
需要普通马达根本做不到的精度

618
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:20,100
好在我们手里还有超立方体可以用

619
00:12:20,100 --> 00:12:24,866
借助它们搞出了几台"四维马达"，刚好能胜任这活

620
00:12:25,366 --> 00:12:28,000
等整套戴森球结构封装完成之后

621
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:31,400
我们的发电量直接拉到三千多亿 EU/t

622
00:12:31,666 --> 00:12:35,033
但这么大的功率，就连超导线都扛不住

623
00:12:35,033 --> 00:12:39,366
我们只好用激光管道，把所有能量转成光来传输

624
00:12:39,466 --> 00:12:40,966
有了这样的发电量之后

625
00:12:40,966 --> 00:12:44,766
我们的 DTPF 终于可以被推到接近"宇宙极限"的强度

626
00:12:44,766 --> 00:12:47,300
甚至可以直接合成时空本身

627
00:12:47,433 --> 00:12:49,200
有了这种划时代的新材料

628
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:54,566
我们造出了"强到能把东西压成黑洞"的马达和活塞

629
00:12:55,066 --> 00:12:58,000
等黑洞被稳定下来之后

630
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:02,000
我们就能利用它的引力场，压任何想压的东西

631
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:05,700
于是我们就有了几乎无限量的超高密度物质

632
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:07,866
比如永恒奇点

633
00:13:07,866 --> 00:13:10,400
现在这种东西多到可以拿来完成每日任务

634
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:12,633

比如用来冲澡或者储存


635
00:13:13,066 --> 00:13:20,100
当然，它们最关键的用途是做
之后游戏会一直用到的最高级线圈

636
00:13:20,100 --> 00:13:21,666
永恒线圈

637
00:13:21,866 --> 00:13:25,700
有了这些线圈，我们就能解锁所有 DTPF 的配方

638
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:31,666
先从时空物质开刀，做到八倍速度
材料消耗只有原来的八分之一

639
00:13:31,866 --> 00:13:37,233
与此同时，我们用旧的海珀珍 DTPF 被动生产无尽

640
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:40,100
速度也不算慢，大概是每小时四百万桶左右

641
00:13:40,100 --> 00:13:45,966
而配方里每一组无尽锭只要用一个无尽催化剂

642
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:49,633
不过这样会很快把我们的燃料用完

643
00:13:49,666 --> 00:13:54,933
问题在于聚变堆根本来不及产出这些燃料需要的前置材料

644
00:13:54,933 --> 00:13:59,800
很明显，聚变技术还得再往上推一档

645
00:13:59,866 --> 00:14:03,633
于是我们开始研究最终版本的聚变线圈

646
00:14:03,633 --> 00:14:07,233
合成计划里粗略看了一圈之后

647
00:14:07,233 --> 00:14:09,233
在那一长串缺的材料里面

648
00:14:09,233 --> 00:14:11,300
我们又一次发现——

649
00:14:11,300 --> 00:14:14,233
铂处理的速度跟不上需求

650
00:14:14,366 --> 00:14:17,700
但这次我们无法确定是哪一台机器掉链子

651
00:14:17,866 --> 00:14:23,500
整片机器群无比复杂的同时，效率还跟不上现在的需求

652
00:14:23,533 --> 00:14:27,266
于是我们把整条铂处理的流程重新过了一遍


653
00:14:27,266 --> 00:14:28,766
想看看哪里还能提速

654
00:14:28,766 --> 00:14:31,200
结果发现：与其优化，不如全拆了重来

655
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:35,766
直接上量子科技，从一堆未精炼的金属粉里硬"抖"出铂

656
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:37,833
这就是我们新的铂处理产线

657
00:14:38,033 --> 00:14:42,233
只靠一台机器，只要灌入电力就能一直往上提速

658
00:14:42,433 --> 00:14:46,833
现在铂的精炼速度是以前的一百倍

659
00:14:46,833 --> 00:14:50,900
我们自然也忍不住想顺手把其他几条产线也一并优化

660
00:14:51,166 --> 00:14:52,666
简单折腾一圈之后

661
00:14:52,666 --> 00:14:58,100
我们才发现这台牛逼的机器甚至
可以把所有的细菌培养缸都给淘汰掉

662
00:14:58,433 --> 00:15:01,466
在彻底重构完我们所有的产线之后

663
00:15:01,466 --> 00:15:05,600
新的聚变反应堆只还缺最后一种材料：龙血

664
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:10,500
打龙本身倒是个不错的运动项目

665
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:13,233
但那绝对算不上龙血的稳定来源

666
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:14,966
尤其是考虑到我们这种夸张的用量

667
00:15:14,966 --> 00:15:17,433
即使是有无限生成的世界

668
00:15:17,433 --> 00:15:20,966
我们还是会让它濒临灭绝

669
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:25,033
为了解决这个问题，我们叫了几位朋友过来商量对策

670
00:15:25,233 --> 00:15:27,433
结果商量变成了恶魔召唤

671
00:15:27,433 --> 00:15:30,033
那只恶魔用自己的心脏跟我们交易了些绿宝石

672
00:15:30,233 --> 00:15:32,766
我们则用这东西做出了一个无限之蛋

673
00:15:32,766 --> 00:15:36,266
这个蛋可以源源不断地给我们提供龙血

674
00:15:36,966 --> 00:15:42,833
有了稳定的龙血供应
我们终于把紧凑型聚变堆升级到 MK-V 最终版

675
00:15:43,366 --> 00:15:45,633
在这样离谱的聚变能力加持下

676
00:15:45,633 --> 00:15:48,500
等离子燃料的产量直接起飞

677
00:15:48,500 --> 00:15:52,100
这也让我们有资本把整片 DTPF 集群疯狂扩容

678
00:15:52,366 --> 00:15:54,400
在这么多台等离子锻炉同时开工的情况下

679
00:15:54,400 --> 00:16:00,400
我们现在能量产用来批量做量子电路的无尽时空和调律源金

680
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:04,966

量子电路是用来控制 UXV 机器的最高阶电路


681
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:09,266
这也意味着我们现在可以到处安装无线能量仓

682
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:14,766
现在我们只需要按下 Ctrl+C、Ctrl+V，基地就开始指数级长大

683
00:16:14,766 --> 00:16:17,000
而且还不用到处拉电线

684
00:16:17,266 --> 00:16:23,500
不过机器数量指数增长，发电量也得跟着指数级翻倍

685
00:16:23,866 --> 00:16:28,033
虽然再多造几个戴森球倒也不算多麻烦

686
00:16:28,033 --> 00:16:32,066
但做戴森球用的那些零件需要很多超时空金属

687
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:37,800
现在我们在"用了三套戴森球发电量的高炉"里烧这种金属

688
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:40,366
结果看下来，还是远远不够用

689
00:16:40,900 --> 00:16:44,400
就在我们快要彻底绝望、感觉一切都陷入黑暗的时候

690
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:47,466
熔炼区域里突然亮起了一道全新的光

691
00:16:47,966 --> 00:16:50,600
那并不是我们的聚变堆要炸了

692
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:53,566
而是一座由诸神亲手赐下的巨型锻炉

693
00:16:53,900 --> 00:16:55,766
在这台巨无霸机器里

694
00:16:55,766 --> 00:17:01,166
我们找到一个能把所有高阶材料
统统高速处理完的专用模块

695
00:17:01,366 --> 00:17:03,433
为了向诸神表达我们的感谢

696
00:17:03,433 --> 00:17:06,766
我们决定亲手建一座史上最大的金字塔来敬仰他们

697
00:17:07,033 --> 00:17:10,366
要搞出那座金字塔，我们需要海量的石头

698
00:17:10,366 --> 00:17:16,300
最省事的收集方式是把整颗星球
塞进一台叫鸿蒙之眼的机器里

699
00:17:16,900 --> 00:17:21,400
当然，这么逆天的机器，它要的零件就已经够折腾了

700
00:17:21,466 --> 00:17:24,033
真正麻烦的是把所有东西组装在一起的那一步

701
00:17:24,566 --> 00:17:26,666
因为我们没有时间可供挥霍

702
00:17:26,666 --> 00:17:34,366
我们要把六套戴森球的发电量全塞进装配线里
把制造速度拉满

703
00:17:34,733 --> 00:17:37,066
没过多久

704
00:17:37,066 --> 00:17:39,866
第一台鸿蒙之眼总算是建成了

705
00:17:40,166 --> 00:17:46,300
这台机器两个小时就能生产两亿四千万单位的石头粉

706
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:48,233
那听起来好像已经很多了

707
00:17:48,233 --> 00:17:52,500
但考虑到我们一开始就已经攒了九十多亿，其实也就那回事

708
00:17:52,700 --> 00:17:54,900
如果我们真想惊艳诸神

709
00:17:54,900 --> 00:17:57,866
我们得升级自己的时空压缩技术

710
00:17:57,866 --> 00:18:02,033
直到鸿蒙之眼的内部空间大到能整个塞下漆黑世界

711
00:18:02,033 --> 00:18:05,900
这样一来，就能一次性榨出超过十亿单位的石头粉

712
00:18:06,033 --> 00:18:08,766
不过，这并不能解决速度问题

713
00:18:08,766 --> 00:18:10,833
说不定还会让问题变得更严重

714
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:15,266
所以如果我们想让这个流程在可以接受的时间内完成的话

715
00:18:15,266 --> 00:18:18,966
我们还得继续升级自己的时间膨胀技术

716
00:18:19,300 --> 00:18:21,466
想做到这一点可一点都不轻松

717
00:18:21,833 --> 00:18:25,700
我们发现的第一个问题是需要的夸张的无尽数量

718
00:18:25,700 --> 00:18:34,433
好在经过八个小时的不断运行，彻底打穿维度边界
再加上跨维度对齐矩阵的加持

719
00:18:34,433 --> 00:18:36,766
我们的 DTPF 终于实现了完全收敛

720
00:18:36,766 --> 00:18:39,166
由此解锁了完美超频

721
00:18:39,166 --> 00:18:44,100
于是我们的无尽产量直接暴涨到每小时五十亿桶

722
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:47,900
但代价是等离子燃料的巨量消耗

723
00:18:47,966 --> 00:18:53,166
多到就算一整塔的终极聚变堆全开，照样跟不上这消耗速度

724
00:18:53,266 --> 00:18:54,366

感谢诸神


725
00:18:54,366 --> 00:19:00,433
它的煅炉可以装一个等离子制造模块
刚好能补上我们燃料上的窟窿

726
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:04,600
有了这套配置，我们终于造出了第一台鸿蒙之眼

727
00:19:04,600 --> 00:19:07,633
不过它还是太慢了

728
00:19:07,833 --> 00:19:11,800
理论上可以靠更高级的时间膨胀场发生器给它提速

729
00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:13,800
但那玩意儿要吃矮星物质

730
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:16,766
而矮星物质又只能靠鸿蒙之眼自己产

731
00:19:16,833 --> 00:19:19,900
唯一的办法是把机器超频

732
00:19:19,900 --> 00:19:23,566
也就是用四倍的能耗，换来两倍的速度

733
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:27,233
这再一次导致能源问题

734
00:19:27,233 --> 00:19:30,366
而且这次的规模大得离谱

735
00:19:30,466 --> 00:19:33,300
大到几乎和天上星星的数量一个量级

736
00:19:33,300 --> 00:19:35,666
毕竟我们已经造了这么多戴森球

737
00:19:35,666 --> 00:19:38,100
都快把能用的恒星用光了

738
00:19:38,100 --> 00:19:40,666
最后只剩一个方向可试——

739
00:19:40,666 --> 00:19:41,466
反物质

740
00:19:42,033 --> 00:19:44,666
把反物质产量堆到一个像样的水平后

741
00:19:44,666 --> 00:19:48,266
就把它们塞进湮灭矩阵，一口气把电池充满

742
00:19:48,266 --> 00:19:55,666
接下来就是在"反物质产量"和"鸿蒙之眼的超频程度"之间
找一个合适的平衡点

743
00:19:56,066 --> 00:20:01,500
答案其实很直接，继续堆更多反物质就对了

744
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:05,266
一直堆到鸿蒙之眼升到鸿蒙层级

745
00:20:05,633 --> 00:20:08,500
当然，造一台肯定不够

746
00:20:08,900 --> 00:20:14,233
说实话，就算二十台鸿蒙之眼，对后面的计划也远远不够

747
00:20:14,266 --> 00:20:16,100
我们还需要更多石头粉

748
00:20:16,100 --> 00:20:18,166
可照现在这套做法，还是太慢

749
00:20:18,466 --> 00:20:23,866
我们的方案是把一台鸿蒙之眼压缩成一个星阵

750
00:20:23,866 --> 00:20:26,666
这样产能就能呈指数级飙升

751
00:20:26,900 --> 00:20:32,433
同时也提醒了我们：从这个微宇宙里拿到的不止石头粉一种

752
00:20:32,566 --> 00:20:35,833
我们还会获得大量浓缩原始恒星等离子体混合物

753
00:20:35,833 --> 00:20:40,100
这些都能拿去给诸神之锻炉供能

754
00:20:40,566 --> 00:20:42,433
只要把燃料投入继续拉满

755
00:20:42,433 --> 00:20:45,400
它的熔炉功率就能再往上推

756
00:20:45,433 --> 00:20:49,400
更关键的是，这是在向诸神展现我们的诚意

757
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:52,700

也能帮助我们在这条"超凡"路上继续前进


758
00:20:52,966 --> 00:20:57,100
这也提醒我们：礼物要打包得体，才能拿得出手

759
00:20:57,333 --> 00:21:00,000
在把一个"Error 级"电池充满后

760
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:04,800
我们把这些石头打包进人造宇宙存储元件

761
00:21:05,466 --> 00:21:08,833
直到这一步我们才反应到：我们有个致命的理解错误

762
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:14,200

我们没法献上"这史上最大的金字塔"
因为我们的工厂还在不断继续产出更多石头


763
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:17,666
而且产能还在指数级往上飙

764
00:21:17,666 --> 00:21:21,700
今天送出去的规模，与明后天一比就像个笑话

765
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:26,433

在被自己之前的想法困了好久之后


766
00:21:26,433 --> 00:21:29,166
我们总算看到了一点曙光

767
00:21:29,666 --> 00:21:32,066
我们不必做一个"一次性礼包"

768
00:21:32,066 --> 00:21:34,200
改成持续投递就行

769
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:35,500
但是当然

770
00:21:35,500 --> 00:21:40,200
想把东西送到星辰之外的那个维度
需要一扇非常强力的传送门

771
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:41,233
也就是星门

772
00:21:41,233 --> 00:21:46,500
问题在于，"超时空马达"无法承载我们这份礼物

773
00:21:46,500 --> 00:21:53,600
而"时空马达"又缺少跨越更高维度的能力，根本到不了那边

774
00:21:53,833 --> 00:21:56,433
所以我们得另做一种全新的马达

775
00:21:56,600 --> 00:22:01,833
这次从"把现实的四种基本物质混在一起"开始

776
00:22:01,833 --> 00:22:03,600
合成出本源物质

777
00:22:03,866 --> 00:22:07,100
然后再加上一些相当复杂的材料

778
00:22:07,100 --> 00:22:09,800
我们做出了一批宇宙素纳米蜂群

779
00:22:10,066 --> 00:22:13,700
我们把它从从纳米锻炉搬到聚爆压缩机

780
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:21,666
我们在这里把纳米蜂群压缩成磁流体约束恒星物质

781
00:22:21,800 --> 00:22:24,900
这种材料将是我们新马达的基础

782
00:22:24,900 --> 00:22:28,433
但我们还缺一些东西才把这种"不可能的流体"彻底定型

783
00:22:28,433 --> 00:22:34,000
对本源物质进行量子操控，析出永恒物质，就能解决这个问题

784
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:36,100
不过要把全部材料彻底融合

785
00:22:36,100 --> 00:22:38,266
还得借助聚爆压缩机

786
00:22:38,266 --> 00:22:42,000

并加上一些高级技术来收容这份新材料


787
00:22:42,100 --> 00:22:44,166
把整套工序跑完之后

788
00:22:44,166 --> 00:22:49,366
我们终于造出了一种强度足够高、
可以运输这座越长越大的巨型金字塔的新马达

789
00:22:49,866 --> 00:22:53,066
接下来就是把这种马达量产出来

790
00:22:53,066 --> 00:22:56,433
于是我们又对工厂进行了一轮升级改造

791
00:22:56,566 --> 00:23:00,200
先是检查我们的聚变塔是否足够好

792
00:23:00,233 --> 00:23:03,833
然后给鸿蒙之眼加装更多的星阵

793
00:23:04,100 --> 00:23:06,766
接着再堆更多的装配线

794
00:23:06,933 --> 00:23:09,900
继续给鸿蒙之眼叠星阵

795
00:23:09,900 --> 00:23:10,966
再多上几条装配线

796
00:23:11,466 --> 00:23:29,833
（字幕已阵亡）

797
00:23:30,500 --> 00:23:34,033
把一路上给到的支线全都做完之后

798
00:23:34,033 --> 00:23:37,000
我们总算准备好去打最终 Boss 了

799
00:23:37,166 --> 00:23:43,766
为此，先把所有鸿蒙之眼合并成一台，堆到 1000 个星阵的规格

800
00:23:43,966 --> 00:23:49,600
再用上一套凡胎肉眼无法直视的
龙之研究反应堆配置

801
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:51,900
刷出足量的混沌碎片

802
00:23:51,900 --> 00:23:54,633
做出几个奇点合成存储器

803
00:23:54,633 --> 00:23:57,466
这样就能一口气把星门直接合成出来

804
00:23:57,600 --> 00:24:03,500
最后再开秘技：双持物质操纵者完成最终挑战

805
00:24:03,900 --> 00:24:06,300
正当我们以为彻底搞定的时候

806
00:24:06,300 --> 00:24:11,066
才发现真正有价值的并不是那一大堆石头粉

807
00:24:11,066 --> 00:24:13,500
而是我们一路建起来的机器们

808
00:24:13,833 --> 00:24:18,633
于是顺着星门另一头飘来的评论

809
00:24:18,633 --> 00:24:22,433
决定更进一步——再造 10 座星门

810
00:24:22,433 --> 00:24:30,566
把这个所谓“现实”的模拟世界算力榨到极限
又连续干了整整一周之后

811
00:24:30,566 --> 00:24:33,300
这项任务终于宣告完成

812
00:24:33,833 --> 00:24:38,200
到这一步，我觉得这座工厂已经强到可以自己继续成长了

813
00:24:38,200 --> 00:24:41,466
那我们也可以放心奔赴下一段冒险了

814
00:24:41,666 --> 00:24:42,600
拜拜

815
00:05:06,366 --> 00:05:11,166
（*湿件电路）

816
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:35,766
（在neta量子操纵者的名字quantum force transfomer）

